<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">
STATUS REFERENCE: Recognised as a full species (
<taxonomicName box="[735,917,259,284]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis box="[735,917,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Zosterops virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation author="White, C. M. N." box="[966,1179,259,285]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" refId="ref30728" refString="White, C. M. N. (1963) A Revised Check List of African Flycatchers, Tits, Tree Creepers, Sunbirds, White-eyes, Honey eaters, Buntings, Finches, Weavers and Waxbills. Government Printer, Lusaka, 122 pp." type="book" year="1963">White 1963: 92–93</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moreau, R. E." box="[1232,1436,259,285]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" refId="ref29199" refString="Moreau, R. E. (1967) African Zosteropidae. In: Paynter Jr., R. A. (Ed.), Check-List of Birds of the World. Vol. 12. Museum of Comparative Zoology, Cambridge, Massachusetts, pp. 327 - 337." type="book" year="1967">Moreau 1967: 333</bibRefCitation>
(both include 
<emphasis box="[306,388,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">atmorii</emphasis>
Sharpe, 1877 and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sundevall, 1850" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[589,880,294,321]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis box="[589,685,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">capensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[693,880,294,321]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), and by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, N. &amp; Bowie, R. C. K." box="[981,1332,294,321]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" pagination="822 - 823" refId="ref29855" refString="Smith, N. &amp; Bowie, R. C. K. (2005) Zosterops capensis. In: Hockey, P. A. R., Dean, W. R. J. &amp; Ryan, P. G. (Eds.), Roberts' Birds of Southern Africa, 7 th edition. John Voelcker Bird Book Fund, Cape Town, pp. 822 - 823." type="book chapter" year="2005">Smith &amp; Bowie 2005: 823–824</bibRefCitation>
(who include 
<emphasis box="[219,301,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">atmorii</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[315,435,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">caniviridis</emphasis>
Clancey, 1962, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[663,759,331,356]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis box="[663,759,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[959,1054,331,356]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis box="[959,1054,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). See the taxonomic note in 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, N. &amp; Bowie, R. C. K." pageId="30" pageNumber="551" pagination="822 - 823" refId="ref29855" refString="Smith, N. &amp; Bowie, R. C. K. (2005) Zosterops capensis. In: Hockey, P. A. R., Dean, W. R. J. &amp; Ryan, P. G. (Eds.), Roberts' Birds of Southern Africa, 7 th edition. John Voelcker Bird Book Fund, Cape Town, pp. 822 - 823." type="book chapter" year="2005">Smith &amp; Bowie (2005)</bibRefCitation>
: 822–823), who state that “neither green (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[807,929,367,392]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="capensis" variety="virens">
<emphasis box="[807,929,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. v. virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[984,1158,367,393]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" variety="caniviridis">
<emphasis box="[984,1158,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. v. caniviridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) nor grey (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[1285,1436,367,392]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="capensis" variety="capensis">
<emphasis box="[1285,1436,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. v. capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[204,340,403,428]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" variety="atmorii">
<emphasis box="[204,340,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. v. atmorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) morphs are genetically distinguishable based on present sampling; we have taken the conservative route and subsumed 
<taxonomicName box="[434,609,439,465]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" variety="caniviridis">
<emphasis box="[434,609,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. v. caniviridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[696,818,439,464]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="capensis" variety="virens">
<emphasis box="[696,818,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. v. virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1017,439,464]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" variety="atmorii">
<emphasis box="[881,1017,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. v. atmorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[1103,1253,439,464]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="capensis" variety="capensis">
<emphasis box="[1103,1253,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Z. v. capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="551" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">
<collectionCode box="[199,251,475,501]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: Sundevall in his original description (1850:101) mentioned both males and females. According to his acquisition catalogue and catalogue of duplicates in combination, he must have had 
<specimenCount box="[1261,1436,511,537]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
at hand for the description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[476,805,546,573]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 34–35)</bibRefCitation>
referred to NRM 568709 [6675] as a “type”; which we treat as a 
<typeStatus box="[262,370,583,609]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this male collected 
<date box="[780,966,582,609]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" value="1840-08-15">
15 August 
<quantity box="[907,966,583,609]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6736" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" unit="in" value="1840.0">1840</quantity>
</date>
in Durban. The 
<specimenCount box="[1157,1384,583,609]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">four paralectotypes</specimenCount>
are: NRM 568710 [6676], a female collected 
<date box="[644,804,619,645]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" value="1840-06-12">
12 June 
<quantity box="[745,804,619,645]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6736" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" unit="in" value="1840.0">1840</quantity>
</date>
in Durban; NRM 90140115 [6674], a male collected 
<date box="[151,378,655,681]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" value="1843-09-24">
24 September 
<quantity box="[319,378,655,681]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68122" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" unit="in" value="1843.0">1843</quantity>
</date>
in Matlapengberg; NRM 90140114 [6673], a male collected 
<date box="[1059,1207,655,681]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" value="1840-06-29">
29 June 
<quantity box="[1151,1207,655,681]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6736" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" unit="in" value="1840.0">1840</quantity>
</date>
in Pietermaritzburg; and a male [4703] collected 
<date box="[474,693,691,717]" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" value="1839-09-30">
30 September 
<quantity box="[637,693,691,717]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.67106" pageId="30" pageNumber="551" unit="in" value="1839.0">1839</quantity>
</date>
in Durban and sent on exchange to 
<collectingRegion box="[1103,1173,691,717]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="30" pageNumber="551">Berlin</collectingRegion>
in 1853 (but not found in the ZMB database).
</paragraph>
